SUMMARY
================================================================================

The PageFire source code is released under the MIT License (see LICENSE), which
permits self-hosting, modification, and redistribution for any purpose —
including internal commercial use — at no charge.

This Commercial License applies if you intend to:

  (a) Operate PageFire as a hosted / cloud service for third parties
      (i.e., you are the operator and your users are the tenants), OR

  (b) Distribute a product or SaaS whose primary value is derived from
      PageFire's publishing infrastructure without building substantial
      additional functionality on top of it.

In other words: **run it yourself = MIT, free forever**.
Resell it as a cloud service to others = contact us.

================================================================================
WHAT YOU CAN DO UNDER MIT (no commercial license needed)
================================================================================

✓ Self-host PageFire on your own server for your own use or your team
✓ Use PageFire in your AI / MCP workflow to publish content
✓ Modify, fork, and redistribute the source code
✓ Build products on top of PageFire (as long as you are the primary user)
✓ Use pagefire-mcp (the npm connector) freely in any project

================================================================================
WHAT REQUIRES A COMMERCIAL LICENSE
================================================================================

✗ Offering a multi-tenant PageFire hosting service where paying customers
  deploy via *your* instance (e.g., a white-label "Pages-as-a-Service")
✗ Bundling PageFire as the core infrastructure of a commercial SaaS product
  where the publishing capability is the primary feature being sold

